f6845119-d02a-4780-9f18-0d5ca378305a.0afe440e-fc30-4311-9938-047a3ace6d09.description=Iterates through a list of values. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. f6845119-d02a-4780-9f18-0d5ca378305a.125d8be4-b4c0-477e-89e5-dbb38be3b9b3.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Inputs\: notifydata - The message to notify the user of. notifyMethod - The method of notification (file, email, display). subject - This is a description of what the notification is about. destination - for files, the file to write to, for emails the email to send to. notificationServer - If the specified method send the notifyData to a server, this is the name of the server to notify (i.e. an email server) from - This is the originator of the message (email from address). sourceServer - Some integrations use a multi-level server architecture for processin tickets, this is the name of a mid-tier server in such an architecture. serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. username - A username to use when authenticating to a notification method requireing authentication. password - The password for username. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. f6845119-d02a-4780-9f18-0d5ca378305a.b3fddcbd-ebdb-4cf1-b8ec-12d96feceafe.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
f6845119-d02a-4780-9f18-0d5ca378305a.baa0e2c1-7bf6-43b3-a276-92e8810a0cc5.description=
Adds a value into the global context (available to all parent and child flows)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

f6845119-d02a-4780-9f18-0d5ca378305a.description=
This flow crawls a website and finds pages with dead links. It then returns a report on which pages contain dead links, and what the dead links are.

Inputs\:
baseURL - This is the url to start crawling from. All pages linked from this page, or any other page given a full crawl will be crawled.
allowedDomains - This is a comma-separated list of domains that can be recursed into. It automatically includes the domain of baseURL.
notifyMethod - How the user should be given the results of the flow.

Responses\:
success - The flow succeeded, no bad links were found.
failure - The flow failed.
diagnosed - Some bad links were found.
flow.name: Find pages with Dead Links
